==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overissue
<hw>O"ver*is"sue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An excessive
issue; an issue, as of notes or bonds, exceeding the limit of capital,
credit, or authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>overissue</qex> of government paper.</q>
<rj><qau>Brougham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overissue</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overissue
<hw>O`ver*is"sue</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To issue in
excess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overjealous</ent>⟦br⟧
